{
  "name": "NovaMind Cred-Stuffing / Brute-Force Response (portal.novamind.ai)",
  "description": "Fires on the CF-Access-CredStuffing scheduled STAR alert (rule 2519093004283366750) — a burst of failed POST /login responses (401/403/429) against the NovaMind employee portal, grouped per src_ip+host. Account-attack playbook: extract the attacking src_ip, gate all downstream work on it being present, then run S1 SDL enrichment (recompute the failed-login volume + distinct User-Agents for the IP, and look for a successful login from that same IP = account-takeover tell) plus AbuseIPDB reputation. Decision branch: if the IP is reputationally malicious OR the recomputed failed_logins is very high OR a login from that IP already succeeded, hard-contain (Cloudflare IP Access block + escalate the portal zone to Under Attack + add an S1 IPV4 IOC + note + raise confidence to SUSPICIOUS + notify SOC). Otherwise apply a lower-risk managed challenge (step-up) and note/monitor. Handles both attack shapes: one IP many passwords (brute force) and one IP replaying many credentials with rotating User-Agents (stuffing) — distinct_uas is the corroborating stuffing signal. run_automatically is false so an analyst approves the destructive path from the Singularity Response console. Evidence discipline: verdict is capped at SUSPICIOUS by automation; the block is gated on an independent AbuseIPDB verdict or a successful-login foothold.",
